text.tspan: Unemployment rate in people with vs. without disability, 2024

Unemployment rate is the share of the
labor force
without work, but actively looking for a job and available to
start soon. A person with a disability is defined as someone limited in the kind or amount of activities they can
do due to a long-term health problem.

Unemployment rate in persons with disability
(plotted on a logarithmic axis)

Unemployment rate in persons without disability
(plotted on a logarithmic axis)
Note: Employment is defined in line with the 13th ICLS and includes the production of goods for own use, such as subsistence farming.
